but I have never seen your actual LMStudioService.cs.

If your service currently looks like:

public class LMStudioService
{
    private readonly HttpClient _client = new();

    ...
}

then the test framework you pasted cannot work.

The test requires dependency injection.

You need something like:

public class LMStudioService
{
    private readonly HttpClient _httpClient;

    public LMStudioService(
        string endpoint,
        string model,
        HttpClient? httpClient = null)
    {
        Endpoint = endpoint;
        Model = model;

        _httpClient = httpClient ?? new HttpClient();
    }
}

or:

public LMStudioService(
    HttpClient httpClient,
    string endpoint,
    string model)
{
    _httpClient = httpClient;
}

Without that, the mock factory is useless because the test cannot inject the fake client.


